<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <link rel="website icon" type="png" href="" />
    <!-- Font Awesome -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/all.min.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/framework.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/master.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/course.info.css" />
    <!-- Google Fonts -->
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Open+Sans:wght@300;400;500;600;700;800&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <title>Course Content</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <!-- ///////////////////// Script in the Header Components ////////////////////////// -->
    <div class="scroller"></div>
    <!-- /////////////////////////////////////////////// -->
    <!-- Start header -->
    <%- include('./components/header.ejs', { avatarUrl: user.avatarUrl,
    currentPage: "courses" }) %>
    <!-- End Header -->
    <!-- Start course information -->
    <section>
      <div id="bottom">
        <a
          href="/courses/course_info/course_lessons?course=<%= courseId %>"
          class="img-link"
        >
          <div class="bottom-left-image">
            <img
              src="<%= courseData.categories === 'kids' ? '/images/learn-now-kids.png' : '/images/learn-now.png' %>"
              alt="Bottom Left Image"
              class="kids-img"
            />
            <button class="learn-buttom">Learn Now</button>
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class="course-head">
        <div class="left-head" id="intro">
          <video
            src="<%= courseData.videoUrl %>"
            controls
            autoplay
            muted
          ></video>
        </div>
        <div class="right-head">
          <div class="course-name">
            <h2 id="course-name"><%= courseData.name %></h2>
          </div>
          <div class="course-info">
            <div class="info">
              <div class="categories">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-list"></i>
                <p id="categorie"><%= courseData.categories %></p>
              </div>
              <div class="duration">
                <i class="fa-regular fa-clock"></i>
                <p id="duration">
                  <%= courseData.duration %> / <%= courseData.lesson %> lessons
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="language">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-volume-high"></i>
                <p>Course Language: Arabic</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="learn" id="learn">
              <a
                href="/courses/course_info/course_lessons?course=<%= courseId %>"
              >
                <button>Learn Now</button>
              </a>
            </div>
            <div class="share" onclick="openShareModal()">
              <i class="fa-solid fa-share-nodes"></i>
              <p>Share Course</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="course-content">
        <div class="about">
          <div class="left">
            <h3>About this course</h3>
            <p id="about">
              <% if (courseData.categories === "kids") { %> Today, we're going
              to learn a cool game - it's called "Sign Language," and it's going
              to be a lot of fun! Explore New Words! We'll be learning new words
              that you use every day, like letters, days, colors, and even
              fruits! Why Learn Sign Language? Learning sign language helps us
              communicate better with our friends and family who might use it.
              It helps us understand each other and be even better friends! And
              that's not all! If you learn sign language, you'll be able to
              discover a whole new world of friends and exciting adventures! Are
              you ready to start? Let's kick off the fun and learn sign language
              together! <% } else { %> This course introduces the principles of
              sign language by initially reviewing the most important words used
              in our daily lives. It covers various topics such as the alphabet,
              weekdays, colors, family, household items, clothing, accessories,
              fruits, beverages, food, vegetables, and unified Egyptian and
              Arabic numbers. This course will make it easier to communicate
              with a person who is deaf or hard of hearingâ€”be it a family
              member, friend, colleague, or neighbor. Learning sign language
              will also give you the chance to get to know many of the people
              who use it, and will allow you to discover a whole new world of
              opportunities. <% } %>
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="right" id="about-img">
            <img src="<%= courseData.categories === "kids" ?
            '/images/kids-about.png' : '/images/adult-about.png' %>" alt="man
            img" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="benefit">
        <div class="head">
          <h3>By the end of this course, you will be able to</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="center">
          <div class="one">
            <p>
              Some of the words and sentences you can use in sign language to
              communicate with someone who is deaf or hard of hearing.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="two" id="benfit-img">
            <img src="<%= courseData.categories === "kids" ?
            '/images/benfit-head-kids.jpg' : '/images/benfit-head.png' %>"
            alt="girl" />
          </div>
          <div class="three">
            <p>
              How to understand a deaf person introducing themselves, and how to
              introduce yourself to a person who is deaf or hard of hearing.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bottom">
          <div class="four"><p>The benefits of learning sign language.</p></div>
          <div class="five">
            <img src="/images/benfit-bottom.png" alt="sign" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="section-content" onclick="toggleContent()">
        <h2>Course Content</h2>
        <div class="section">
          <p>Section 1 : Sign Language</p>
          <i class="fa-solid fa-plus" id="icon"></i>
        </div>
        <div id="section1-content" class="contents">
          <% courseData.Lessondescription.forEach((lesson, index) => { %>
          <p
            class="<%= index === courseData.Lessondescription.length - 1 ? 'last' : '' %>"
          >
            Lesson <%= index + 1 %> : <%= lesson %>
          </p>
          <% }) %>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="share-on" id="shareModal">
        <div class="share-content">
          <span class="close" onclick="closeShareModal()">&times;</span>
          <p>Share on:</p>
          <div class="share-links">
            <a href="#" class="share-link">Facebook</a>
            <a href="#" class="share-link">Twitter</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <%- include('./components/footer.ejs') %>
    <!-- End course information -->
    <script src="/js/course-info.js"></script>
    <script src="/js/lang.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
